  "highlights_url": "https://www.formula1.com/en/video/race-highlights-2025-singapore-grand-prix.1845152565530127617",
  "event_preview": "Marina Bay Street Circuit measures 4.927 km (3.061 mi) and features 19 turns winding through the heart of Singapore's financial and civic district, around the shores of Marina Bay. The venue hosts Formula 1's original night race — the first in the sport's history when it debuted in 2008 — and remains the most demanding event on the calendar in terms of physical endurance, with cockpit temperatures exceeding 50°C and an average race duration approaching two hours. The circuit has long held a unique distinction: a safety car appeared in every single edition from its inception until the streak was finally broken in 2024. Hemmed in by concrete barriers throughout its 19 corners, the layout demands absolute precision and rewards qualifying position above almost anything else — two-thirds of races here have been won from pole. The official race lap record stands at 1:34.486, set by Daniel Ricciardo for RB during the 2024 Singapore Grand Prix, while the all-time qualifying lap record belongs to Lando Norris, who clocked a 1:29.525 for McLaren in Q3 of that same weekend.",
